org.openbel.framework.core.protonetwork
Class ProtoNetworkMerger

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.core.protonetwork.ProtoNetworkMerger

public class ProtoNetworkMerger
extends Object

ProtoNetworkMerger merges two ProtoNetwork objects together. This operation is mostly a union of the two proto networks, except for the term tables which treat each entry as unique. For example, given the two statements: 

 geneAbundance(EG:207) :> rnaAbundance(EG:208)
 geneAbundance(EG:208) :> rnaAbundance(EG:310)
the merged parameter will be: 
 (union)
 207
 208
 210
whereas, the merged terms will be: 
 (additive)
 geneAbundance(#)
 rnaAbundance(#)
 geneAbundance(#)
 rnaAbundance(#)
The result of the merge will be in protoNetwork1.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

Method Detail

merge

public void merge(ProtoNetwork protoNetwork1,
                  ProtoNetwork protoNetwork2)
Merge the second proto network, protoNetwork2, into the first proto network, protoNetwork1. This will union each field of the two proto networks, except terms, which will be combined with possible overlap.

Parameters:
protoNetwork1 - ProtoNetwork, the first proto network, which cannot be null
protoNetwork2 - ProtoNetwork, the second proto network which cannot be null
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if either protoNetwork1 or protoNetwork2 is null.
